Loved seeing my vision for an epic 80’s party come together for another year of fun with a group of amazingly cool clients at Splitsville Luxury Lanes in Downtown Disney!  This was one “totally rad” celebration featuring lots of eighties entertainment, themed arcade areas, a band and DJ, glow bar and checkerboard dance floor. Favorite elements were the giant pac man and ghost decals added to glass walls, lots of vintage arcade games like Pac Man, Centipede, and Donkey Kong. I loved arranging a selection of fun and nostalgic 80’s candy in a tempting display accented with a Light Bright sign reading “I Want Candy”. My favorite design creation was twin giant sized replicas of hot pink cans of Aqua Net, with real misting action! This added so much fun to the lighting and dance floor area. I’ll be sharing more righteous details of the awesome entertainers and lots more peeks at all the totally 80’s details to come! #80sparty #eightiesparty @downtowndisneydistrictanaheim @splitsville.anaheim #corporateevents #spicoli  #eightiesparty #80sband #80smusic #downtowndisney

The entertainment at this incredible “Back to the 80’s” party in Downtown Disney was provided by my all time favorite entertainment company: the LA Follies. 

I’ll be sharing more awesomely fun videos of this totally tubular group of jazzercizers and rollerskating divas all week. The talented 80’s crew made the party SO much FUN! 

They engaged the crowd, had guests rolling with their hilarious moves, and kept the 80’s energy up like Lionel Richie - all night long!

The raddest 80’s party on the planet wouldn’t be complete without the gnarliest 80’s band of all time! Wayward Sons rocked all the dudes and dudettes like a hurricane at Splitsville in Downtown Disney Anaheim this year, it was a night of epic nostalgia - these long haired music masters deliver a rock music punch, and they do it with swagger in leather pants! The power packed, guitar riffing, drum blasting and wailing vocals of this 80’s rock show had the dance floor packed all night, movin’ to the greatest songs of the 80’s! Wayward Sons hit all the high notes and topped it off with engaging antics. They really Poured Some Sugar on the crowd, working the party into Hysteria with spot on renditions of 80’s favorites from Journey, Queen, Styx, Bon Jovi, Foreigner, Boston, Guns N’ Roses, Def Leppard and more! #80smusic #80sparty #80sband ##rockband #80sconcert #80stribute ##ocevents #eventplanner #bandforhire #waywardsonsofficial #waywardsons #waywardson #ilove80s ##80srock #downtowndisney #downtowndisneydistrict #partyplanner #corporateevent #corporateevents #orangecounty @waywardsonsofficial @lafollies @splitsvilledtd

Memories of @snapconf 2018, still can’t believe I pulled off this epic dessert and crafty themed bash for opening night! “Eat Dessert First” was our theme, and if you were there you may STILL be coming down from the sugar high! We jazzed up our faces with sprinkles and makeup at the Sprinkle Beauty Bar, then dressed up as desserts as we decorated Kunin felt hats as cupcakes and sweet treats using a favorite die for @sizzix  by Elena @charitywings !  We made amazing one of a kind canvas aprons from @canvascorpbrands , they were loaded up with trims and embellishments from @expointlhtx (check out the hashtag #snapyourapron to see some of the fun creations!) my friends @floracraft donated a bajillion blooming flowers and foam to create stunning flower cakes, these were displayed as the centerpieces on dozens of dazzling cake stands from @amalfidecor. Can you believe we gave them all away at the party!? @thermoweb offered a cupcake-topper-making station that everyone super loved! I can always count on @orientaltrading for the best in party props, candy and decor, and @sparklingice kept us all well hydrated with yummy beverages! We also got to delve into wood burning, and created some “magic mixing spoons” with wood burning kits from @plaidcrafts. Besties @curiouschase and @hipiera from @evite (they’ve since moved on to other fab endeavors) naturally managed our super sweet invites, and offered a fun and creative candy kabob making station! We decorated cupcakes and made iced sugar cookies baked up by the awesome Little America Hotel in Salt Lake City, and had lots of prizes from @consumer.crafts, and from me, Ritzy Parties! ❤️ Thanks sooo much again to all of the amazing and generous sponsors, people are still talking about this one to this very day! Let’s never ever forget my incredible team of ladies who donned the cotton candy wigs and made this happen @avintagegirlshop @superradlaura @alovelydesign @staciesplaceofficial @partieswithacause @fernandmaplestyle @charitywings @midgepalmer @midgeandmadgemingle Trish and Rhonda, too! #snapconf #eatdessertfirst #sugarhigh #sugarrush #snapconf2018 #partyplanner #corporateevents #sponsors #eventplanner #crafttherainbow

Your Halloween won’t be complete without a Purple Poisoned Mushroom cocktail! This delectable mix of gin and florals is made even more hauntingly delicious when dripping with Blueberry Rimlicks and Dragonfruit Juicy Enhancer from the new Chef Rubber mixology line, Cock Tailor. 
Recipe:
3 oz Empress Indigo Gin
.75 oz Torani Lavender Syrup
.5 oz Belvoir Farm Elderflower Syrup
1/2 teaspoon Cock🍸Tailor Dragonfruit Juicy Enhancer
Cock🍸Tailor Blueberry Rimlicks
Pink Nonpareils or sanding sugar 
Flashy Ice Cube and Plastic Spider accent 

Melt Blueberry Rimlicks in microwave 20-30 seconds at a time until melty
Dip the rim of your glass in the rimlicks and let ‘er drip
When nearly set, dip in the pink nonpareils, tilting to gather more of the sprinkles. Set aside to firm.

In a cocktail shaker half-filled with ice, add the gin, syrups and dragonfruit powder. Shake furiously. Think of your enemies. Shake harder. 
 
Pour into prepared glass and add a flashy LED ice cube set to green, accent with a plastic spider. 

Cheers! This drink will have immediate effects on the sense of health and well being. Listen, I didn’t say they’d be good effects. It ‘s called a poisoned mushroom, after all.

Stop scrolling. I just invented the YUMMIEST no-cook dessert for the holidays. It turned out so beautiful and delicious, it feels like a crime to get this much taste sensation and elegance out of such a simple recipe, but here goes!

Ingredients:
1 tub Cozy Shack Rice Pudding
Caramel Rim Licks  1 Tbsp Honey Powder *
1/2 cup chopped dried fruits, such as figs, apricots, and cherries
Amaretto Virgin Spirit Enhancer *
Ground Nutmeg
Whole dried figs

Optional: honey or hot honey 

Presentation:
Mini round cups*
Birch straws cut into picks

Combine the rice pudding with honey powder and stir well until thoroughly mixed in. Set aside. 
Rim the cups with caramel rim lick and allow to set. Add two tablespoons of the rice pudding mixture to each cup. Sprinkle in a layer of the chopped dried fruit and spritz once per cup with amaretto virgin spirit enhancer. Fill the remainder of cup with rice pudding. Top with a whole dried fig and decorative accent like paper birch straws cut into short pieces. I love to grind a bit of fresh nutmeg on top. Serve chilled, this is a fast, inexpensive and delectable sweet treat for your fall table. Drizzle with honey or hot honey for an extra delicious treat. Getting into the holiday spirit with this fun craft mocktail gift. It’s easy and affordable to make! Just add all the dry ingredients in a jar, then place in a gift box with a couple bottles of your favorite booze-free craft cocktail, like the No. 7 from @curiouselixirs. Here’s how I made this one, I call it a Christmas Tea Party:
16 oz Mason Jar with Lid 
1 teaspoon ground ginger
1 teaspoon CockTailor Honey Powder 
1/2 teaspoon Ground Nutmeg 
1/2 cup mixed dried fruits, I used cranberries, cherries, apricots and figs 
2 whole cinnamon sticks
2 slices CockTailor Fruit Fetish Blood Orange Slices
Two spritzes CockTailor Amaretto Virgin Spirit Enhancer
1 packet Bergamot Tea
Four Sugar Cubes

Add all items to the jar and close tightly.
Gift with two bottles of Curious Elixir No. 7. 

To enjoy, remove tea bag from package and place in jar. Then, add 16oz water and steep in the refrigerator for 2-6 hours. Serve chilled over ice with Curious Elixir No. 7 for a tasty holiday craft cocktail that won’t get you sleighed. 

These are so much fun to make, for an extra fun touch add your own gift tags and instructions to a festive box with some paper shred or tissue paper, pop in an ornament or some pinecones, (I love to add disco balls), and twirl in a little curl of ribbon. #mocktail #christmasdrinks #boozefreelife #nonalcoholicdrink #diygifts #curiouselixirs #cocktailor #chefrubber #chefrubberparty #ritzyparties

Merry Christmas and Happy Holidays! If there’s one thing I’ve learned in 14 years of event planning, it’s how to create opportunities for guests to connect, engage, have fun and be creative together. This year, we kicked off my own family Christmas with an ornament painting party. We had the best time! First, I set up a station with paint palettes, brushes, wipes and paper towels, acrylic paint in a rainbow of colors, glitter paints, and of course a selection of plaster ornaments. Then, we reused the paper bags from our holiday shopping by cutting them into placemat-sized rectangles to protect the table. Some cordless tabletop lighting was super helpful to get into the details. Our millennial kiddos really appreciated my paint choice, DecoEarth, since it’s made from recycled house paint. We sparkled things up with Galaxy Glitter and Craft Twinkles, too. You know I just love a little razzle on my dazzle 🥳. I’m so impressed with my entire family’s creative ornaments, I think they turned out so amazing! Most of all, I loved having this time together, making such fun memories during the holidays. #ornamentpainting #decoearth #viviluxusa #vivilux #crocodilewipes #familyactivities #christmasparty #decoart

Cheers to 2024! Anyone else totally fine with leaving 2023 in the dust? The past year has been wild. I’ve been quietly navigating a bajillion big challenges with health, family, friendship and business. Sometimes 2023 felt like a circus! Here’s a shuffle through all the fun and festive themed holiday foods we tried at Disneyland and California Adventure last week We loved the Festival of Holidays Tasting Passport offered by California Adventure Park. There were a huge variety of unique holiday cocktails and mocktails, too! Between the four of us, we tried several. Favorites were the Mango Candy Cocktail, Espresso Martini, and kid friendly Particle Punch with Exploding Bits. We also sampled a Sparkling Rose Wine, Berry Pomegranate Paloma and Ginger Pear Mule with an edible orchid!
